commit_message:
Use more backends in existing tests

This allows us to start defining test suites for common capabilities /
allowed failure modes.

Null Backend:
    test_decode_with_missing_parity
    test_decode_with_missing_multi_parity

Jerasure RS Vand:
    test_decode_with_missing_parity

Jerasure RS Cauchy:
    test_decode_with_missing_parity

ISA-L RS Vand:
    test_decode_with_missing_parity
    test_get_fragment_metadata_crc32

ISA-L RS Cauchy:
    test_decode_with_missing_parity
    test_get_fragment_metadata_crc32

SHSS:
    test_decode_with_missing_parity
    test_get_fragment_metadata_crc32

liberasurecode RS Vand:
    test_decode_with_missing_parity

Change-Id: I9ee9ec3d8f86a10c4c7b5d6425a530b9c44d1156

commit_message:
Make test format strings consistent with test function names

* When we specify a particular backend, we don't need to include it in
  the display string; we'll already include it in the output.

* test_destroy_backend_invalid_args shouldn't be reported as
  test_create_backend_invalid_args.

* Consistently include the leading "test_" in the display string.

Change-Id: Ibd72ba4ae609ad77e8808aa1594b0adb62e34ef0

commit_message:
Remove deprecation warning from tempest tests

Tempest deprecated tempest.test.requires_ext() function in
Ibd52153d00b8e60fb8c89e38d94e358ddc787251
Now it is available in tempest.common.utils and this patch changes
all Neutron tempest tests to use this new function.

Change-Id: I49e0672379f87f5402e782ad7f3dc8e6f5c6d5ad

I'm not really convinced.  The problem here is for something like nodepool, with long-term builders doing a build every day, if we're actually leaking every build that adds up and eventually messes up the builder.

We don't expect anything to have files on the mount point still open.  I would like to know what the root cause is here.  It doesn't seem we have enough information ATM.  Something might have started during the build ... I would rate that as a bug.

One thought, if you'd like to investigate, is to wrap the unmount call with a check.  If it fails with the busy message, do as it suggests and at least dump into the logs an lsof grepped for the mount point.  This would give us a clue as to what the real problem is here.  Then we can make a better decision about what to do"}, {'account_id': 7016, 'date': '2017-08-04 17:05:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Failed to open parameter YAML error while trying to unmount imagedir

When trying to build a new VM image for cloud in SUSE distro
after the image is converted to qcow2, it tries to unmount
the image_dir that was mounted and fails, since it is busy.
The 'umount -f' is not able to forcefully umount the tmpfs partition.
So changing it to 'umount -l' fixes the problem.

Change-Id: Ieff1b369df1f81e2b58a21f78df62f751a31d7e1
Closes-Bug: #1708509

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-09-08 22:34:41.000000000', 'message': 'Skip unnecessary Unicode decoding

If you pass a UTF-8-encoded str[1] to json.dumps(), it is correctly
serialized with Unicode escapes in the JSON output. This lets us
remove a couple of unnecessary decodings.

Added tests to prove that this is true.

[1] Python 2, of course. On Python 3, the phrase "UTF-8-encoded str"
means that the speaker is confused.

Change-Id: Idd34b2ec33c146300da1d557f03d176dfedfee63
'}, {'created': '2017-09-08 23:23:22.000000000', 'message': "Improved tests for non-ASCII objects

There's some necessary[1] Unicode handling in the container server
that was untested and could be removed without any tests failing; this
adds coverage.

[1] its removal breaks plain-text container listings from the
container server

Change-Id: Idd34b2ec33c146300da1d557f03d176dfedfee63
"}]
commit_message:
Improved tests for non-ASCII objects

There's some necessary[1] Unicode handling in the container server
that was untested and could be removed without any tests failing; this
adds coverage.

[1] its removal breaks plain-text container listings from the
container server

Change-Id: Idd34b2ec33c146300da1d557f03d176dfedfee63

When Mistral services are configured with systemd, the services time out
on shutdown. The root cause is that each of the server thread is
assigned to a different instance of the oslo.service ServiceLauncher.
The ServiceLauncher can manage multiple server threads. When the server
threads are added to the same instance of the ServiceLauncher, SIGTERM

commit_message:
Fix services launcher to handle shutdown properly

When Mistral services are configured with systemd, the services time out
on shutdown. The root cause is that each of the server thread is
assigned to a different instance of the oslo.service ServiceLauncher.
The ServiceLauncher can manage multiple server threads. When the server
threads are added to the same instance of the ServiceLauncher, SIGTERM
is handled properly for each server threads.

Change-Id: I8b739844f6073890324189aee028c0d7da3cc76e
Closes-Bug: #1714351
(cherry picked from commit 8a4fe7f146446201d88237804e007c8987814622)

commit_message:
Scope vars references correctly when delegated

In my environment, my computes have "untagged" venvs, so the path
to the venv on nova_compute hosts has "nova-untagged" instead of
"nova-<tag>", meaning this tasks breaks because it is delegated from
computes to a conductor host, but does not use the conductor vars to
reference the location of nova's venv.

Change-Id: I3967cbad0cbcc2214db1ca1f2225f3d140fd1774

commit_message:
Updating import for linux/interface opts

neutron-lbaas imports neutron/agent/linux/interface.
This conf option is being refactored and moved to
neutron/conf/agent/linux. This patchset updates
import statements.

Change-Id: I3a48725e0fc48523430ebc915fd265c7c6e489bf
Partial-Bug: #1563069
Depends-On: Ib1e0e63dec2985c417412d1ecc68e2a74ef87182

commit_message:
Fix unit and functional tests

For unit and functional:

The commit d00a50aad11465d904663dea14b3814017bcff75 moved the
plugins.ml2.config module to conf.plugins.ml2.config

For functional tests only:

Modify the post_test_hook.sh script to accomodate the new changes in
os-testr. This fix for networking-ovn is basically a copy & paste from
the neutron one [0].

[0] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/503138/

Change-Id: I4fbcbfdd6d5f9fa77414df15302da517f23986bd

commit_message:
Suppress curl warning w/shell module

Using curl from the shell module generates an Ansible warning.
This patch adds "warn: no" to suppress the warning.

Change-Id: I83a52173aea5e5574d4d1acee16ebad95845ff5e
(cherry picked from commit c40827db06510945b2c933546ec0ffb0f0b34a1a)

commit_message:
Replace pmap shellout with pure python implementation

Without this patch, the pmap -XX call fails on openSUSE Leap
distributions as those have a fairly ancient procps version that
does not support the -XX parameter. A pure python implementation
is more portable, faster and even shorter than the subprocess
call.

Closes-Bug: #1716066
Change-Id: I2fdb457e65359a1c9d40452c922cfdca0e6e74dc

commit_message:
Make resource_cleanup stable

Add docstrings, unit tests and an helper for class resource
cleanup. Check super's resource_cleanup is invoked when
overriden to ensure the cleanup stack is processed.

Change-Id: I9c89ba4efd715634dde6b1182c2025ddf9c2f7d2

commit_message:
Add a validation resources fixture

Make validation resources available via a fixture that can be used
by tests conveniently via the useFixture helper.
Add unit tests for it and the validation resources module in general.

This work in preparation to move validation resources to lib.

This commit introduces the RegistryFixture which sets up a usable
registry to unit tests of features that do not rely on configuration
but need a registry. The fixture cleans up the registry once the
test is over and this uncovered the fact that a few tests
erroneously dependent on the registry being populated - which just
happened to be because of some other tests.

Which the new registry fixture in use, such unit tests have to be
fixed in this patch.

Change-Id: I0faaff07e446e35537b53289fc8980f6692fcf55

'}]
commit_message:
Revert "Tag workflows created by the templates"

This reverts commit a7a02f0da866c66dce9757a42bf56144cfa70d5a.

This change requires a heat functionality which is not yet available so scenario001-containers job fails because of the new tags.  Reverting to unblock CI and this should be back after we have heat promotion

Change-Id: Ib0fed291c1c4e41d1ea0bb7fc2ccbdabac1d336b
Closes-Bug: #1716915

'}]
commit_message:
Add RoleConfig output to major_upgrade_steps.j2.yaml

I96ec09bc788836584c4b39dcce5bf9b80e914c71 added this output to the
deploy-steps.j2, but missed adding this to the major upgrade template
which means the overcloud RoleConfig output is broken after the upgrade
(until the converge update switches back to the deploy-steps.j2 derived
template)

Closes-Bug: #1716404
Change-Id: I331fa18b456ca2d6c124316d513374e3fe5a5007
(cherry picked from commit 27018b4182d77abf612697cfe54a4fc3ceeb6be5)

commit_message:
Trust certificate based on fingerprint

This commit gives us the possibility of choosing to trust a
certificate based on comparing the server's certificate fingerprint
to a fingerprint that we can provide as a configuration option (via a
kernel cmdline argument). This fingerprint is calculated by using
the SHA256 algorithm and using a resulting hex string.

Note that if no fingerprint is given from the configuration, a check
is not done and IPA proceeds to the same path it had before.

The workflow given a fingerprint is as follows:

* Check if the API URL is configured to use 'https' and if the
  fingerprint was given.
* Fetch the server's certificate.
* Compare the server's certificate fingerprint to the given
  fingerprint.
* If the comparison failed, an exception is raised.
* If the comparison passes, the certificate is written to a temporary
  file and later used to create the requests session, being set as a
  trusted certificate.

Closes-Bug: #1616495
Change-Id: I59b9694bfb04afdcd0d1ec08efae447b7a6e356d

commit_message:
DellEMC ScaleIO chart to configure secret and StorageClass

New ScaleIO chart to configure StorageClass in order
to leverage ScaleIO volumes through new client
introduced in Kubernetes 1.6. OpenStack charts like
mariadb can leverage ScaleIO volumes for their storage
needs.

Reference to ScaleIO Kubernetes client.
https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/tree/master/examples/volumes/scaleio

Previously attempted to submit this code https://review.openstack.org/#/c/465695/2
Pete Birley and Michal Dulko suggested to create the scaleio chart under openstack-helm-infra
so here it is!

Change-Id: I60faf248a9c33f08e8c677bee619c8fe96ad3724
Signed-off-by: Eric Caron <eric.caron@emc.com>

commit_message:
Add script to run glance-api over httpd

This was mostly based on Heat and it's meant to be used as the
WSGI script, configured in httpd.

Change-Id: I891371c0c7f381441507386653280777fb8560d3

subject: Deploy glance-api over Apache httpd

commit_message:
Remove manual heat metadata URL setting

This was added as a workaround[1] for a puppet-heat bug which was fixed
and backported[2].

[1] I57c9e7010bfe4afc6e62fb4c3406716d11cdfa28
[2] I90ccdd881a41d803e28064f44b821ab48a6fa8ea

Change-Id: I4eb759cbdb4307465065b639c2539088e83f5016

commit_message:
Suppress rsync warnings w/command

Ansible throws warnings when we use rsync with the command
module. This patch suppresses those warnings.

Change-Id: I42652318f128120b1ecec4781066c89ee9023636
(cherry picked from commit 20801aa010f8914a9399b02508fc56188b111be2)

commit_message:
Pike doc clean up

Several clean up performed in this patch:

* remove readme in the doc/source
* move installation.rst and usage.rst to the new userdoc/
* add api.rst to userdoc/
* add introduction.rst in doc/source
* add index.rst in every folder
* add release info in every spec

Change-Id: I9ea96993f916b753cc1aa16c2ea2983b93922f23
Signed-off-by: zhipengh <huangzhipeng@huawei.com>

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-09-12 14:23:51.000000000', 'message': 'Fix output for subnet show

The use_default_subnet_pool column is never returned by the API, it is
only being used in the request to create a subnet. So make sure that we
do not show it when displaying a subnet.

Change-Id: Ie021149cceb8f89b779ad0f3c13ac60420509671
Related-Bug: 1668223
'}]
commit_message:
Fix output for subnet show

The use_default_subnet_pool column is never returned by the API, it is
only being used in the request to create a subnet. So make sure that we
do not show it when displaying a subnet.

Change-Id: Ie021149cceb8f89b779ad0f3c13ac60420509671
Related-Bug: 1668223

commit_message:
Run zuul-migrate job on changes to mapping file

When we make changes to the zuul/mapping.yaml file, run the zuul-migrate
job so that we can see how those changes update the output.

Change-Id: Ib1cac8be499fab280490cbe5a48372b80ff60cf8

Let's hold this until the 4.0 feature branch that will open up next month."}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2017-05-22 19:37:08.000000000', 'content': 'Topic changed from remove-profile to feature-4.0'}, {'account_id': 8246, 'date': '2017-07-20 07:31:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

where are we for this?

senlinclient package has been waiting for a year for this ...

We promised that the senlin command line interface are to be removed by April this year.'}, {'account_id': 6482, 'date': '2017-07-20 14:17:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2

i think we can remove this now, dtroyer?'}, {'account_id': 2472, 'date': '2017-07-20 14:26:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

Signaling this removal is going to be interesting. We can raise the major version number of orc-lib, but most users are going to be looking at the version of osc, not the lib.'}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2017-07-21 20:14:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

I think we need to coordinate the major versions of osc-lib and osc for things like this, ie this option can go into osc-lib 4.0 which will not be used by prior versions of osc, requiring a <4.0 cap for osc.  That leaves us with a 3.x series should we need it, but I doubt we will.

I want to do feature branches for 4.0 soon so we can start mering the accumulating backward-incompatible features.'}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2017-08-03 19:14:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

We (inadvertently) merged https://review.openstack.org/474050 in July that did the same thing.  That should not have happened but the damage is small in this case, the --profile option was only (formerly) used by OSC itself.

The problem is in the process failure and sorting out how to make incompatible lib changes synced with OSC.'}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2017-08-03 19:14:46.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}, {'account_id': 8246, 'date': '2017-09-12 12:42:56.000000000', 'content': "Restored

There is no reason why a feature that has been marked to be deprecated for over one year (and three release cycles now) cannot be removed.

We have been warning the users that senlin CLI will deprecated by April 2017 for we believed that OSC lib will remove this flag by then. We rejected all revisions that tried to to do the right thing only because this thing is here. And it seems to me now it is gonna be here forever.

I really don't get the reason why such a deprecated flag is so sticky. We are trying to be good citizens in the community so we waited, with great patience."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2017-09-12 14:38:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

[{'created': '2017-05-18 02:11:47.000000000', 'message': "Remove support to deprecated '--profile' option

The '--profile' option was planned to be removed one month ago. This

commit_message:
Remove support to deprecated '--profile' option

The '--profile' option was planned to be removed one month ago. This
patch actually kills it.

commit_message:
Update vif_attach from NeutronVIFPortIDMixin

This patch updates vif_attach from NeutronVIFPortIDMixin to rely
on presence of Neutron. Drop incorrect logic that skips mac_address
update when show_port() to neutron failed as NeutronVIFPortIDMixin
is used only in flat and neutron network interfaces which require
neutron presence.
Update api tests to use real neutron port.

Change-Id: Iffaf3569aa296b4466729cf7f62c92995b6b3723

commit_message:
Revert "Retire openstack-ansible-security"

This reverts commit ea9b39d723a07e2e9bcb2f4a9b423144c93f92bc.
In order to release stable/pike we need this to still be present.
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/502063/ is failing.

Once we release stable/pike we can figure out how to properly remove
this repository.

Change-Id: I50308b1c3001371d4554b6c2640bd5384e870a53

commit_message:
Flatten out RDO simple mapping list

In attempt to not have to re-wrap list every time
you add a new package to the list and make it easier to
keep it sorted, flatten it out to one per line

Change-Id: Icece77abaeedb2f6db4f6ced5b41422475a45f63
Depends-On: I424df8dbf38a8275c96713e1a8bcf38f37869e8e

commit_message:
Add missing features to multi-node-aio

The multi-node-aio update that moved the provisioning from bash to
ansible dropped a few features that we use for gating purposes.  This
commit re-adds the following:

1. The ability to drop iptables rules to do port redirection from the
   host to private IPs.  This is controlled by CONFIG_PREROUTING and
   the ansible variable mnaio_host_iptables_prerouting_ports.
2. /etc/hosts on the physical node is now updated w/ the hostname and
   IP of each VM so we can access VMs by name.

NOTE: With #1, we redirect to the VM's DHCP address, and not it's
      management address.  The latter seemed to the desired address
      but didn't work, which is why we've resorted to DHCP.  If using
      this address is incorrect please note so we can investigate
      further.

Change-Id: Ib194c314280f2474a2e4dac6d0feba44b1ee696f

The DVR path was missing logic to avoid triggering DB updates
even if the status was already correct. This was leading to a
constant back-and-forth updating between the agent and the server
effectively not changing anything but the updated_at timestamp
and the revision_number.

Closes-Bug: #1716522
Change-Id: I88c678ac8a562db91c71edbc71dc43d1ada6c452

commit_message:
Don't trigger DVR port update if status the same

The DVR path was missing logic to avoid triggering DB updates
even if the status was already correct. This was leading to a
constant back-and-forth updating between the agent and the server
effectively not changing anything but the updated_at timestamp
and the revision_number.

Closes-Bug: #1716522
Change-Id: I88c678ac8a562db91c71edbc71dc43d1ada6c452
(cherry picked from commit 1edd0c792499dbd6c59257a10c901360941dbcf6)

commit_message:
redhat/packages: set allow_virtual to True

RDO packaging provides virtual packages. Puppet 3 is setting
allow_virtual to False and in 4 it's set to True.
Force it to True to avoid issues when deploying RDO.

Change-Id: I54ade4cb4add005429840eb7d8970d736b1a0b22

commit_message:
configure devstack to use merged bagpipe-bgp

That includes:
* dropping the submodule pointing to github's bagpipe-bgp
* installing exabgp from github master
* switching bagpipe_bgp entry points to point to the correct module
* adapting the startup script for bagpipe-bgp
* disabling bagpipe-bgp ARP proxy (not compatible with gateway fallback)
* enabling debug logging based on environment
* setting no BGP peers (because we only have single node devstack CI jobs)
* pinning looking glass and exabgp log level
* adding an optional b-bgp-lg service that triggers a periodic
  bagpipe-looking-glass
* adding log colourization :)

Change-Id: I085a617464f71b5f94f9802215bbb8f0cc6b604d

commit_message:
Withdraw doc for bgpvpn-routes-control API extension

Next release feature freeze is close, and it's not realistic to expect
that the implementation-in-progress of the bgpvpn-routes-control API
extension will be ready in time.

To avoid confusion, this change reverts the parts of change
Ib2cefcb6a345887435b754fbdcff3584329d45d2 that are documenting
the new bgpvpn-routes-control API extension.

The intent is to revert this change once an implementation is finished.

Related: blueprint routes-control

Change-Id: I97146127959cc0161892da5fef65c2a4a1598886

> (1 comment)

 > The code looks good to me. What I don't slightly understand now is
 > whether the fact that we still have two facilities (thread manager
 > and process manager which are, in fact, oslo service and process
 > launchers) solves the problem with correct handling of SIGTERM? If
 > all components started with one launcher then I'd understand that
 > but we still have two.
 > 
 > Thanks

What I understand is, the API service always needs high throughput for requests processing, using multi-processes could utilize more processor cores in the host. The initial design comes from Nova, followed by Neutron, then the code moved to oslo.service as a common lib.

However, I am not sure if putting single process service behind a wsgi server (e.g. uwsgi, gunicorn, etc.) will get the same effect. If yes, then I think we could use one service pattern."}, {'account_id': 8731, 'date': '2017-09-04 03:21:00.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Yes, this explanation is correct. If you pay close attention to how we run all the components then you'll see that we use ServiceLauncher for engine, execution and event engine and ProcessLauncher for API. ProcessLauncher allows to use multiprocessing capabilities (look at the module with the same name) to increase APIs throughput w/o having to launch many API processes manually.

So, Winson, I think it's ok then given that you always run API separately. I think it actually should be a recommended way."}, {'account_id': 8731, 'date': '2017-09-04 03:21:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 9712, 'date': '2017-09-08 08:05:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2017-09-08 08:05:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: -Verified

commit_message:
Fix services launcher to handle shutdown properly

When Mistral services are configured with systemd, the services time out
on shutdown. The root cause is that each of the server thread is
assigned to a different instance of the oslo.service ServiceLauncher.
The ServiceLauncher can manage multiple server threads. When the server
threads are added to the same instance of the ServiceLauncher, SIGTERM
is handled properly for each server threads.

Change-Id: I8b739844f6073890324189aee028c0d7da3cc76e
Closes-Bug: #1714351

commit_message:
Revert "update constraint for os-testr to new release 0.8.2"

This reverts commit 4d4898bb094515bc9232a7e4cbf097fa0a939c6a.

os-testr 0.8.2 switches to stestr which needs to be agreed to
in the PTI. It also breaks projects that are not expecting it.

commit_message:
Manila-UI breaks Horizon's "Network" panel group

Since the OpenStack Pike release, the Manila UI dashboard integration
for Horizon breaks the "Network" panel group, causing the "Network
Topology" panel to fail and the buttons "Create Network", "Create
Router", "Create Security Group" and "Allocate IP To Project" to
silently disappear from the panels "Networks", "Routers", "Security
Groups" and "Floating IPs".

This commit adds the parameter "targets" to the method
"tenant_quota_usages" that was introduced by the fix of Horizon
Bug#1675504.

Closes-Bug #1715540
Signed-off-by: Christoph Fiehe <fiehe@gmx.de>

Change-Id: I6d8f9ae2ae03577e63cc985d37fcbba824d68a9d
(cherry picked from commit f49f885b32f750c19cda619fa0290ea36503dc98)

commit_message:
Added etcd wrapper recipe

- This recipe implements a basic etcd installation for shared oslo configs.
  A wrapper recipe is needed for instantiation, as etcd is a pure library
  cookbook.

Change-Id: Id2f934a9fc408276cb0a25afc2f65ec5f5c54c15

commit_message:
Remove the duplicated success message

The workflow now sends a success message the following message. So when
tripleoclient prints a similar message it is then duplicated.

    "Successfully introspected all nodes."

Closes-Bug: #1716855
Change-Id: Ia4c88459a1a95f7f4e5a57a57a9ca8265c6e01f7

commit_message:
Initial common Pike updates

- Bumped chefdk to 1.6.1
- Switched release to pike
- Added is_release attribute for testing, defaults to false
- Added RDO deps repo for testing pre-release packages
- Added ubuntu-cloud proposed repo for testing pre-release packages
- Switched the default linter to cookstyle
- Normalized the banner message
- Dropped pip installation method for python-openstackclient since the
  packages are fresh enough

Change-Id: I7a67ba2520b8e44efec6edd8506f96b0e0dc913b

Devstack fails on s390x, as there was no etcd3 binary hosted
on github like it is for other architectures.

The current workaround for s390x is to disable etcd3 in local.conf.

allows the installation of etcd3 for s390x if an alternate download
URL is provided via local.conf

service is enabled.

In the long run the issue gets solved once distros provide the etcd3 package.

commit_message:
Add etcd3 support for s390x

Since [1] devstack is failing on s390x with "Distro not supported".
The reason for this is the missing etcd3 support. It worked before
[1] as we were able to disable etcd3 via local.conf. But as etcd3 is
a base service, we might not be able to rely on this workarond in
the future anymore.

As there is no etcd3 binary hosted on github like it is for other
architectures, the user needs to specify an alternative download
URL via local.conf. Otherwise devstack will exit with an appropriate
error message.

  ETCD_DOWNLOAD_URL=<custom-download-url>

[1] https://github.com/openstack-dev/devstack/commit/d8bb220606737719bcdf7c5b4f54906f2974c71c

Change-Id: I1c378a0456dcf2e94d79a02de9d3e16753d946d6
Partial-Bug: #1693192

iso8601.UTC is correct datetime UTC field object.
iso8601 >= 0.1.12 includes only iso8601.UTC for python3
while both UTC and Utc() for python2. Less then 0.1.12
included both UTC and Utc() for both python2/3.

Change-Id: I0f8796fba6725eea013b3f8d9ad33c10a402c524
Closes-Bug: #1715486
'}]
commit_message:
iso8601.is8601.Utc No Longer Exists

iso8601.UTC is correct datetime UTC field object.
iso8601 >= 0.1.12 includes only iso8601.UTC for python3
while both UTC and Utc() for python2. Less then 0.1.12
included both UTC and Utc() for both python2/3.

Change-Id: I0f8796fba6725eea013b3f8d9ad33c10a402c524
Closes-Bug: #1715486

> (1 comment)
 > 
 > Lets see if could align with existing templates format.

Hi Saravanan,

Other than in OVS or linux bridge the contrail vrouter does not have multiple member interfaces. With the structure you suggested, users might want to add multiple interfaces, which is not supported.
Contrail vRouter always has one (logical) interface connected. The interface types can be:
- ethernet interface
- bond interface
- vlan interface
This is what we call the bind interface. This bind interface is defined as a standard interface in os-net-config.
For vRouter dpdk mode it will look differently as the bind interface must not be managed by os-net-config. When dpdk driver binds an interface it will disappear from the operating system driver and os-net-config will not see it anymore.

vrouter kernel mode:

#ethernet interface:
-
  type: interface
  name: nic1
- 
  type: contrail_vrouter
  name: vhost0
  mtu: 1500
  bind_int: nic1

#vlan interface
-
  type: interface
  name: nic1
-
  type: vlan
  vlan_id: 100
  device: nic1
- 
  type: contrail_vrouter
  name: vhost0
  mtu: 1500
  bind_int: vlan100

#bond interface
-
  type: linux_bond
  name: bond0
  use_dhcp: false
  bonding_options: "mode=active-backup"
  members:
  -
    type: interface
    name: nic1
  -
    type: interface
    name: nic2
- 
  type: contrail_vrouter
  name: vhost0
  mtu: 1500
  bind_int: bond0



vrouter dpdk mode:

#ethernet interface 
#(note: nic1 is not defined as it will be bound to dpdk driver and as such be invisible to os-net-config): 
- 
  type: contrail_vrouter_dpdk
  name: vhost0
  mtu: 1500
  bind_int: nic1

#vlan interface
#(note: nic1 and vlan interface are not defined as it will be bound to dpdk driver and as such be invisible to os-net-config):
- 
  type: contrail_vrouter_dpdk
  name: vhost0
  mtu: 1500
  vlan_id: 100
  bind_int: nic1

#bond interface
#(note: nic1, nic2 and bond interfaces are not defined as it will be bound to dpdk driver and as such be invisible to os-net-config):
- 
  type: contrail_vrouter_dpdk
  name: vhost0
  mtu: 1500
  bind_int: nic1,nic2
  bonding_options: "mode=active-backup"

#bond/vlan interface
#(note: nic1, nic2, bond and vlan interfaces are not defined as it will be bound to dpdk driver and as such be invisible to os-net-config):
- 
  type: contrail_vrouter_dpdk
  name: vhost0
  mtu: 1500
  bind_int: nic1,nic2
  vlan_id: 100
  bonding_options: "mode=active-backup"


For dpdk the bonding and vlan are not needed as interfaces. The vlan_id, the member interfaces (pci address) and bonding options will be used
as arguements calling the dpdk binary. There is no need to have these interfaces in the system at all.

commit_message:
This patch adds initial support for the Contrail vRouter interface

The patch introduces the Contrail vRouter interface object. It can be
configured as a kernel module or in dpdk mode. The parameters are:
bind_int (required): the interface the vRouter interface is bound to
dpdk (optional): boolean if dpdk or not

Closes bug: 1709862

Change-Id: Iecb739e3964bf5307b0605ea1d80d2369f60918b

commit_message:
Make outward_rabbit pre-checks idempotent

Copy the patterns from the rabbit checks, skip some pre-checks when the
container has already been started. Without this change the pre-checks
fail when you re-run the deploy, i.e. the port is not free because
rabbit is already running on that port.

This bug was triggered because murano is enabled, and this change has
been added to add the extra rabbitmq instance by default:
d8fe3ea780c188b6e937ab6f08a8475d2330a9fa

Closes-Bug: #1715135

Change-Id: I0eb8785e7cd4eadfa792ea14a27f54a891b2bf02

commit_message:
Tag workflows created by the templates

This is useful to easily filter workflows created by the templates
and for a specific stack.

Change-Id: I0a26cacaf5ad5709881043434694c9254a9e710b
Related-Bug: #1715389

commit_message:
Add neutron_driver value to prepare command

OpenDaylight/OVN is not enabled by default in overcloud. A logic needs to be
implemented to create ODL image reference when ODL needs to be deployed and
the same for OVN. This patch adds neutron driver value set depending on the
environment file specified to image prepare command.

Co-Authored-By: Numan Siddique <nusiddiq@redhat.com>
Change-Id: I3e395986ad777b1d6b057bb33fac8d5ed2d3d26a
Partial-Bug: #1713685
Partial-bug: #1699085
(cherry picked from commit d66114a4405c0a319483bdee64bb9e3422ccfb77)

commit_message:
Fixing hyperlink issue

    Fixes a documentation hyperlink issue -:

    * Refer to doc page -:  https://docs.openstack.org/neutron/latest/contributor/internals/openvswitch_agent.html
      for string  "Networking in too much detail"

    * Hyperlink for above string is broken
      It is pointing to http://openstack.redhat.com/Networking_in_too_much_detail#Networking_in_too_much_detail

    * Instead it should point to  http://openstack.redhat.com/networking/networking-in-too-much-detail/

    * This fix would correct the hyperlink on the doc page.

    Closes-Bug: #1712787

Change-Id: I3e62389ffcb415e4baccd27161423c9ecbe3f417

commit_message:
'l2gw' entrypoint for Neutron service_plugins

  Provide a 'l2gw' entrypoint definition, to allow the activation
  of the service plugin in a more friendly syntax.

Change-Id: Ia86f1885a9c9284d8a854891937b56cc9d730399
Signed-off-by: Ricardo Noriega <rnoriega@redhat.com>

commit_message:
update the version of ansible to 2.2.3

pip install uses global pip instead of pip from the
virtual environment. There is a fix posted to
ansible 2.2.1-3
https://github.com/ansible/ansible-modules-core/issues/5347

Change-Id: I5ed3ff5da4af4710381047cd46274e7b7af97022

commit_message:
Remove original CentOS Ceph repos in tripleo-ci master

Remove original CentOS Ceph repos in tripleo-ci master so that the
mirrors introduced in Ie055a95f6d5ca8ca704d8b30407b99f3948dad20 will
be used instead.

Change-Id: I0f821817a9ae606350af632530d702c756b4c0e8

commit_message:
Add mapping for unversioned names

On SUSE, the main package starts usually with python- (eg. python-Babel)
and then the py2/py3 packages with python2- and python3- .
To be able to use pymod2pkg for the singlespec convertion, also an
unversioned name is needed.

Change-Id: I3eed46af4ac8c937222c927516bd1a338200d6f2

commit_message:
Manila-UI breaks Horizon's "Network" panel group

Since the OpenStack Pike release, the Manila UI dashboard integration
for Horizon breaks the "Network" panel group, causing the "Network
Topology" panel to fail and the buttons "Create Network", "Create
Router", "Create Security Group" and "Allocate IP To Project" to
silently disappear from the panels "Networks", "Routers", "Security
Groups" and "Floating IPs".

This commit adds the parameter "targets" to the method
"tenant_quota_usages" that was introduced by the fix of Horizon
Bug#1675504.

Closes-Bug #1715540
Signed-off-by: Christoph Fiehe <fiehe@gmx.de>

Change-Id: I6d8f9ae2ae03577e63cc985d37fcbba824d68a9d

commit_message:
Add API test for port dns_domain

This patchset adds a Tempest API test for the port dns_domain attribute.

It also enables the dns-domain-ports extension for testing, which is a
super-set of the dns extension.

Change-Id: I5c1da61a8a49c190aad549713da646a3abb8ccb1
(cherry picked from commit 39a9e0971688acdf9d787bde80af707a2e16c097)

commit_message:
Refactoring config options for ml2 config opts

Refactoring neutron ml2 config opts to be in neutron/conf/plugins/ml2.
This would allow centralization of all configuration options and
provides an easy way to import.

NeutronLibImpact

Change-Id: Ibc5a9ab268578c243ef13f7e0041bacd6c0c410b
Partial-Bug: #1563069
Needed-By: Id0a97dda7718f06e33b2d30ce01cdcb3e9a46f7d

commit_message:
Cloning a volume from a snapshot in thin lv

To create a volume from a snapshot in thin lv,
we can create a snapshot for the snapshot to
create a volume same as snapshot. And active it.

Change-Id: Ib12752e541f522a9091a2bb2a56bec4193e5f3e7
Closes-Bug: #1707098

commit_message:
Correct docs usage of keystoneauth1 session

keystoneclient.session has been long deprecated in favor of
keystoneauth1.session. This change corrects entries in the
documentation to use the correct library's session.

Change-Id: I6ae71befe62aee567e44308ec9afec2dd34efda1

In cinder.scheduler.flows.create_volume.ExtractSchedulerSpecTask,

is None:
    def execute(self, context, request_spec, volume, snapshot_id,

    def _populate_request_spec(self, volume, snapshot_id, image_id):

The execute should transfer the volume which is a Volume() instance
instead of volume.id which is a string.

commit_message:
Fix wrong param transfer in scheduler flows

In cinder.scheduler.flows.create_volume.ExtractSchedulerSpecTask,
the execute method call _populate_request_spec func if request_spec
is None. The original code shoulud pass an Volume() instance object
instead of volume.id in _populate_request_spec.
Amend the volume.id to volume.

Closes-Bug: #1709034
Change-Id: I4d63f9d0a798fda39cebcd4aa2e610fc1e145da4

commit_message:
Make nova patching parameters configurable in Nuage

Nova patching parameters are available in nova.conf but are not
configurable from tripleo-heat-templates. Exposing these parameters
from Nuage composable services to make them configurable. It enables
setting the patching parameters in environment files. This change
depends on the addition of nova patching configuration parameters.

Change-Id: Iacad25da044f2bac83ee5f577ddcd70650eb61e5
Depends-On: I51ef3e19daff1d98cfe5c2c16475c16e6a3e3e0f

commit_message:
build-images: adjust workaround for libguestfs

This is now fixed in libguestfs-1.36.3-6.el7_4.3.x86_64
so workaround is modified to work with both 7.3 and 7.4
to avoid issue
https://bugs.launchpad.net/tripleo/+bug/1716487/comments/14

Change-Id: Ie3372bfc7b829d4109c1466bd4423c3069e04027

commit_message:
Correct import of keystoneauth1 session

keystoneclient.session has been long deprecated in favor of
keystoneauth1.session. This change corrects the import in the
tests to use the correct library's session.

Change-Id: Ic24ebde59e4b9eb70d6f14c1e0536f8d24f0de73

commit_message:
Handle case with None encoding during std.http action execution

During some cases resp.content may have a context not in json format
and with 'None' in the resp.encoding. Need to properly handle this
situation and don't try to pass 'None' as an argument to decode.

Change-Id: Id87d650996f16b5ffab79d72413134a4c7fe9ca9
Closes-Bug: #1700608
(cherry picked from commit 178369459ff9cc7e0faa1f9dbd9116e24bf7ca12)

commit_message:
[upstream] Adding [operator] tag & other tagging fixes

This patch introduces the operator tag to the tags table
and also adds it the modules that operators might be
interested in. It tags the metrics module with [management],
updates the 'x' in the table to be ' ', and also adds a
heading to the table.

Change-Id: I33eb297ec0d3c83d64bd5c6239918586b1925749

The gating on python 3.4 is restricted to <= Mitaka. This is due to
the change from Ubuntu Trusty to Xenial, where only python3.5 is
available. There is no need to continue to keep these settings.

Change-Id: Ia7d7521faefe3619411e1870a6838915e63df90e
'}]
commit_message:
Remove support for py34.

The gating on python 3.4 is restricted to <= Mitaka. This is due to
the change from Ubuntu Trusty to Xenial, where only python3.5 is
available. There is no need to continue to keep these settings.

Change-Id: Ia7d7521faefe3619411e1870a6838915e63df90e

commit_message:
Move manila backend configuration from pacemaker to base

There is no reason to keep backend configuration in pacemaker-specific
manifest. This configuration is used no matter whether pacemaker is
used or not.

Change-Id: I63b53d230372a323db1d35a3774283ad2e29fbb1
Closes-Bug: #1714310
(cherry picked from commit 7327cc88246abe6473b7b29703af408adeccc88d)

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-09-11 21:21:51.000000000', 'message': 'Enable selinux in containers

We cannot use the --selinux-enabled docker daemon option on CentOS/RHEL 7.3.
It will fail if security_inode_copy_up is not found in the kernel symbols:
https://github.com/projectatomic/docker/blob/docker-1.12.6/daemon/daemon_unix.go#L661
NB this has been reduced to a warning upstream:
https://github.com/moby/moby/commit/885b29df096db1d6746ece4b3a298a1ffe85716d

Instead this just bind mounts /sys/fs/selinux in containers-common.yaml.

Everything appears to work at initial glance. Pingtest succeeds, and
live-migration between baremetal and containerized computes works.

Change-Id: I018221bf7ae9ab9ece193b55f1ce31eb1591046c
Closes-bug: #1715171
(cherry picked from commit 520f889a31f1ea6ee2bad86d1dbb3c0435604d10)
'}]
commit_message:
Enable selinux in containers

We cannot use the --selinux-enabled docker daemon option on CentOS/RHEL 7.3.
It will fail if security_inode_copy_up is not found in the kernel symbols:
https://github.com/projectatomic/docker/blob/docker-1.12.6/daemon/daemon_unix.go#L661
NB this has been reduced to a warning upstream:
https://github.com/moby/moby/commit/885b29df096db1d6746ece4b3a298a1ffe85716d

Instead this just bind mounts /sys/fs/selinux in containers-common.yaml.

Everything appears to work at initial glance. Pingtest succeeds, and
live-migration between baremetal and containerized computes works.

Change-Id: I018221bf7ae9ab9ece193b55f1ce31eb1591046c
Closes-bug: #1715171
(cherry picked from commit 520f889a31f1ea6ee2bad86d1dbb3c0435604d10)

commit_message:
Validate that the specified LB does exist

If we use the specified loadbalancer does exist, we should validate it
in the validate() function. Otherwise, it will attach to a cluster
failed.

To fix this problem,I add some statements in validate() to check the
loadbalancer.

Change-Id: I12ff134da0355701934707d98712bae2281af339
Closes-Bug: 1715070

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-09-05 07:41:05.000000000', 'message': 'Add loadbalancer params to lb_policy

I need attach a loadbalance policy to my cluster with a existed
loadbalancer, but senlin cannot surpport it and it report an error with
" InternalError: Conflict (HTTP 409) (Request-ID:
req-07244d60-04c7-4fdb-b3c1-561e13c93c39)"

So I add three params that loadbalancer,pool id and health monitor id to
LoadBalancingPolicy. Then I add an if statement that check the self.lb if
None or not, if not exists self.lb, creating a loadbalancer and add
members else add member for the loadbalancer existed directly.

Change-Id: I0e5a98c5c6dcd0b4e884d2a4d4dc0a5a8e92ef19
Closes-Bug: 1715070

commit_message:
Add loadbalancer params to lb_policy

I need attach a loadbalance policy to my cluster with a existed
loadbalancer, but senlin cannot surpport it and it report an error with
"Failed in creating loadbalancer: Conflict (HTTP 409)"

To fix this issue I add three params loadbalancer, pool_id and health
monitor id to LoadBalancingPolicy, then add member to the existing loadbalancer
directly other than always create a new one.

Change-Id: I0e5a98c5c6dcd0b4e884d2a4d4dc0a5a8e92ef19
Closes-Bug: 1715070

commit_message:
Don't trigger DVR port update if status the same

The DVR path was missing logic to avoid triggering DB updates
even if the status was already correct. This was leading to a
constant back-and-forth updating between the agent and the server
effectively not changing anything but the updated_at timestamp
and the revision_number.

Closes-Bug: #1716522
Change-Id: I88c678ac8a562db91c71edbc71dc43d1ada6c452

commit_message:
Remove urllib3/requests from requirements

This patch removes urrlib3 and requests from the requirements.txt
file so that the CentOS Ceph gate will pass.

At the moment, yum tries to install python-urllib3 and throws errors
when it finds that urrlib3 files already exist (since they were
installed via pip).

This also breaks our periodic builds which, in turn, makes infra
quite displeased.

Closes-Bug: 1715888
Change-Id: I2a8b0ebcca9839d033552130688356c055f71553

commit_message:
Add sha-1 to list of insecure hashes

With the news of a first collison implemented [1], bandit should
now start blacklisting the use of sha-1.

The sha-1 hash was added to the existing blacklist check B303 which
currently checks for MD5 and variants.

[1]: https://security.googleblog.com/2017/02/announcing-first-sha1-collision.html

Change-Id: I411d8d4aeb4d740635c60b559ecda72ab951b629

add authtoken-middleware

Add authtoken middleware for integrating with the OpenStack Identity API
and handling authorization enforcement based upon the data within the
OpenStack Identity tokens

commit_message:
api-ref: Remove unused parameter defs

During the initial migration of the api-ref docs, there were
several parameter definitions pulled over that are not actually
used anywhere in the docs.

It may be that some of these _should_ be referenced, but at
least as of right now they are not. Rather than carrying them
around on the chance that they could be used down the road, we
should just clean them out for now.

Change-Id: Ic9018608b00705c80df05243647f5c81124610df

commit_message:
Avoid redundant HA port creation during migration

When a router is migrated between DVR+HA and HA(i.e DVR+HA->HA and
HA->DVR+HA), redundant "network:router_ha_interface" ports are created.
For binding a HA router to a agent, existing code can create multiple
ports, but is using only one port and other ports remain still in DB
until router is deleted.

In this patch, when duplicate entry is detected while binding,
we remove the port which is created at that time for binding.

Closes-Bug: 1715370
Change-Id: I0c6c5f9dfce1bf2d99672b5cf9e072bfb0228a17
(cherry picked from commit 5b0165e9407da95dd1d26cd3ba226a939af80582)

commit_message:
Pecan: Add missing body validations

This changes the pecan body validation to bring parity with the
old legacy controller code.

* If a body is present on POST/PUT, it must be a JSON dict
* DELETEs to an item must not contain a body
* A POST request to the standard collection controller must have
  resources in the body.

Closes-Bug: #1714348
Change-Id: I1568285c28d227bacf038b3667466a20d3947ca9

commit_message:
Refactoring agent linux&ovsdb config

Refactoring neutron agent linux and ovsdb config opts
to be in neutron/conf/agent so that all the config options
reside in a centralized location. This simplifies the
process of looking up the config opts and provides an easy
way to import.

NeutronLibImpact

Change-Id: Ib1e0e63dec2985c417412d1ecc68e2a74ef87182
Partial-Bug: #1563069

commit_message:
Pecan: fix logic of hiding authZ failures as 404s

Change [1] altered the behavior of the legacy API controller
to do the sane thing and return an HTTP 403 instead of a 404
whenever a user got a policy authorization failure when trying
to mutate a resource they have the permission to view.

This carries the same logic over to the pecan API.

This also adjusts the logic for GET requests to return 404s
instead of 403s to match the resource hiding behavior of the
old controller.

1. I7a5b0a9e89c8a71490dd74497794a52489f46cd2

Closes-Bug: #1714388
Change-Id: I9e0d288a42bc63c2927bebe9c581b83e6fbe010b
(cherry picked from commit fe8107a8179deca093463bbc95b6ba8b54915bf7)

[{'created': '2017-09-12 15:55:25.000000000', 'message': 'Fix tacker bug in haproxy

Tacker requires SSL to contact its public url. However, the path to the cert
was missing in the haproxy config because the haproxy_ssl option was missing

Change-Id: Ia0cfa9ff5fc5f720b52f9f917296e41805ea41d6
'}]
commit_message:
Fix tacker bug in haproxy

Tacker requires SSL to contact its public url. However, the path to the cert
was missing in the haproxy config because the haproxy_ssl option was missing

Change-Id: Ia0cfa9ff5fc5f720b52f9f917296e41805ea41d6

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-09-12 08:28:36.000000000', 'message': 'Fix barbican-api log filter in fluentd

Barbican-api log is a uswsgi process and fluentd expects as
openstack service process.
This change moves log type to uswgi group.

Change-Id: Ifaf5645d0d19e133e41de0c55a55321fccfc391f
Closes-Bug: #1716513
'}]
commit_message:
Fix barbican-api log filter in fluentd

Barbican-api log is a uswsgi process and fluentd expects as
openstack service process.
This change moves log type to uswgi group.

Change-Id: Ifaf5645d0d19e133e41de0c55a55321fccfc391f
Closes-Bug: #1716513

commit_message:
Pecan: add calls to resync/dirty quota usages

Add calls to dirty and resync the quota engine during
DELETEs and GETs respectively. This matches the old API controller
behavior and will be covered when the unit tests are switched to
use pecan in [1].

1. I76dc23fb7b96d82b0da50285bd0aac76142e81e5

Closes-Bug: #1714389
Change-Id: I1fb6b471e0e7cbf9b10dd14233931be94af38a41
(cherry picked from commit e76a575b0570880d4209ff1ea73f82c01e4a6e24)

commit_message:
Pecan: add plugin pagination/sorting validation

This adds the validation to ensure that the plugin supports
native sorting when native pagination is used.

This patch doesn't add a unit test for this because it will
be covered in the switch to pecan for the existing unit tests
in I76dc23fb7b96d82b0da50285bd0aac76142e81e5 (which is how this
bug was discovered).

Closes-Bug: #1714381
Change-Id: I6443832357c91fe791853a374cdec11dd1f968ea
(cherry picked from commit 31dc80a0c22ae1cbacad1694f799cbdc4228cfd4)

commit_message:
Move to auto-generated CLI reference

This patch enables the cliff.sphinxext sphinx extension and moves our
CLI reference document to be auto-generated from the code.

Note: There is a formatting issue with required arguments that include a
hyphen.  This has been opened as a bug [1].

[1] https://bugs.launchpad.net/python-cliff/+bug/1712612

Change-Id: I726749db4882064ede60f2bbe46e3b185ebc1f52

[{'created': '2017-09-12 15:31:56.000000000', 'message': 'Remove assumption that a valid IPMI channel cannot follow an invalid one

It seems to be incorrect at least for some iLO machines.

(cherry picked from commit d6ff5116f4a5586238d44a196ec89d844b151f9d)

commit_message:
Remove assumption that a valid IPMI channel cannot follow an invalid one

It seems to be incorrect at least for some iLO machines.
Also harden the code against invalid output from ipmitool.

Change-Id: I733785e9c7d86eadca963f0776910504bf91bcfe
Closes-Bug: #1714944
(cherry picked from commit d6ff5116f4a5586238d44a196ec89d844b151f9d)

commit_message:
Revert "Revert "Fix AZ related API docs""

Fix AZ related API docs

While we have a big fat comment in the development docs explaining why it's so
terrible to use default AZ values for either booting an instance or setting
an aggregate AZ metadata, we still have confusing API docs that provide the
wrong name for the AZ...

Fixing that and trying to explain the problem within the docs, too.

This reverts commit 92ca21abd61b6df7fc8bc5ffe7502f03b3eca2dd.

Co-Authored-By: Sylvain Bauza <sbauza@redhat.com>
Co-Authored-By: Stephen Finucane <stephenfin@redhat.com>

Change-Id: Ie4bfe32bbef0f8060bfc0ad4190f262d4a8bd3b2

commit_message:
Add RoleConfig output to major_upgrade_steps.j2.yaml

I96ec09bc788836584c4b39dcce5bf9b80e914c71 added this output to the
deploy-steps.j2, but missed adding this to the major upgrade template
which means the overcloud RoleConfig output is broken after the upgrade
(until the converge update switches back to the deploy-steps.j2 derived
template)

Closes-Bug: #1716404
Change-Id: I331fa18b456ca2d6c124316d513374e3fe5a5007

commit_message:
Update generate_cinder_opts path

The location of the generate_cinder_opts script was moved in
d3abafdee4affe457e39705fd9b8e27b0f80f657. There is a check in
the script to exclude the script to its parsing, but this path
was not updated when it was moved. This updated the path to
the new location.

Change-Id: I369dec534c69f67fea72959bc9d626dddd8768ff

commit_message:
Add support for virtual hosts

Adds the 'pseudo_vhost' option which when enabled will incorporate the
virtual host into the address semantics.  This creates a 'subnet' like
address space for each virtual host.  Use this when the messaging bus
does not provide virtual hosting support.  It is enabled by default as
to date none of the supported AMQP 1.0 message buses natively support
virtual hosting.

It also updates SSL support: SSL can either use the connection
hostname or the vhost name when validating a server's
certificate. This is controlled by the 'ssl_verify_vhost' option.
This option is disabled by default as it requires both vhost and SNI
support from the server.  By default SSL will use the DNS name from
the TransportURL.

Change-Id: I49bb99d1b19e8e7e6fded76198da92ca5f7d65ab
Closes-Bug: #1700835
Partial-Bug: #1706987
(cherry picked from commit 263dce9ea8e52632cc07d101d1859034eb3943c7)

commit_message:
Use ensure_resources to install pacemaker package

Avoids a potential duplicate Package resource
when both the install and remote modules are used.

Change-Id: I9511c1830b967038721e03dcbb4401cc3059648a

commit_message:
Adds Bandit #nosec flag to instances of SHA1

Currently, bandit marks usages of SHA1 as insecure, which
results in false positives for instances of SHA1 in keystone.
However, keystone uses HMAC-SHA1 which is currently considered
secure as opposed to just SHA1 hashing.

This change marks a # nosec comment against the lines which
are triggering the false positives in Bandit in order to
tell bandit to avoid these instances of SHA1.

See [1] for HMAC-SHA1 discussion in keystone

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/453365/

Change-Id: Ibb44db1f8727d014d186b412106d0cd4e2f4a6dd

commit_message:
Remove Xen networking plugin

Since nova-network is deprecated, networking is controlled by neutron.
This plugin here was used by nove-network and will confuse operators.
I tested on my own environment, and it seems safe to remove.

Change-Id: I1b64ea1f5906b0c4dd1d5e311095cfe41e884ff7

commit_message:
Auth parameters: accept and set few default values

After switching to keystone_authtoken, its value are used:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/485521/
but the value of user_domain_name and project_domain_name is
undefined by default when using puppet-sahara: extend
get_keystoneauth_cfg to accept a default value and set it
for those two parameters.

Closes-Bug: #1715681
Change-Id: I8aa51f3f6b0b03c8c41a9a23df3de305552cdc06
(cherry picked from commit 541e02f424fed1a2d0376c1ccb542b46effcd8e5)

commit_message:
[DOC BLD FIX] Correct reST field lists in docstrings

Most common format for documenting arguments is reST field, the
incorrect docstring will cause a Sphinx warning to be generated
and caused the documentation to be improperly rendered.

[1] http://sphinx-doc.org/domains.html#info-field-lists

Change-Id: I8860624c923ebdd3dc64ca52613eb79fd959da2b

commit_message:
Remove usage of config option verbose

oslo.log deprecate config option verbose since aug 1, 2015 in review:
in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/206437/

That was a long time ago so it should be possible to remove it now.
This was already merged once but had to be reverted because some
projects were still relying on it. Oslo team plan to remove it,
so we need clean up its usage before removing it.

Closes-Bug: #1663570

Change-Id: I71a48f64cd329153f7a9b76adfa9d45e6e1b7f24

commit_message:
Replace six.iteritems() with .items()

1.As mentioned in [1], we should avoid using six.iteritems to achieve
iterators. We can use dict.items instead, as it will return iterators
in PY3 as well. And dict.items/keys will more readable.
2.In py2, the performance about list should be negligible, see the
link [2].
[1] https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Python3
[2] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-June/066391.html

Change-Id: If49b2280a3007aaca410a266a35de6f9d680b64e

commit_message:
Replaces uuid.uuid4 with uuidutils.generate_uuid()

Openstack oslo_utils has a generate_uuid function for generating
uuids. We should use that function when generating uuids for
consistency.

commit_message:
Drop MANIFEST.in - it's not needed by pbr

deb-python-os-net-config already uses PBR:-
setuptools.setup(
	setup_requires=['pbr>=1.8'],
	pbr=True)

This patch removes `MANIFEST.in` file as pbr generates a
sensible manifest from git files and some standard files
and it removes the need for an explicit `MANIFEST.in` file.

Change-Id: Id07219aec390a1df5cfc757c93d2c3db5556fdac

commit_message:
Replace the usage of 'manager' with 'os_primary'

In tempest, alias 'manager' has been moved to 'os_primary'
in version Pike, and it will be removed in version Queens [1].

The other usages which also need to be replaced, are listed below:
* admin_manager > os_admin [2]
* os_adm > os_admin [3]
* os > os_primary [4]

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/468036/
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/467852/
[3] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/467605/
[4] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/466991/

Change-Id: Icca46615efa64dda38c0131209638d7c475cd254

commit_message:
Use get_rpc_transport instead of get_transport

With the added get_rpc_transport() function is oslo.messaging
and the recent version bump of oslo.messaging to 5.24.2, we can
safely replace get_transport() with get_rpc_transport() wich is
much cleaner.

Change-Id: I8e58a7a69934cf99bea4f1aca9e3c6e4dba15e37

commit_message:
Replace assertRaisesRegexp with assertRaisesRegex

assertRaisesRegexp was renamed to assertRaisesRegex since Py3.2
For more details, please check:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/
unittest.html#unittest.TestCase.assertRaisesRegex

commit_message:
Merge tag '2.1.58' into debian/newton

Tagger: Andy Grover <agrover@redhat.com>
Date:   Mon Nov 30 15:45:08 2015 -0800

retag 2.1.58 of version 2.1.fb58

  * New upstream release.
  * Using pkgos-dh_auto_install from openstack-pkg-tools >= 53~.
  * Adding a "targetctl" package that holds the init script, so that Debian
    users can decide to use the Python 2 or 3 implementation (previously, the
    Py3 package was depending on the Py2 package).
  * Create /var/target/pr and /var/target/alua when installing targetctl,
    remove them on purge.

Change-Id: I9f8be58b0befa268389872036b60d321c3ff5cf4

commit_message:
Use newer location for iso8601 UTC

Newer versions have moved from iso8601.iso8601.Utc() to
just iso8601.UTC, causing tests to fail under py35.

Change-Id: I9c0bb9f28c2abe3d7c33c4cff4fa1e968aae52ce
Closes-bug: #1715486

commit_message:
api ref for standard-attr-tag extension

This updates the API reference for the tag based extensions by adding
details on the standard attr based tags extension as well as noting
the deprecation of the existing tag based extensions.

Change-Id: I849f8e8dc7c89c99f15881446a5c407281e97b77
Partial-Bug: #1706307

commit_message:
[Api-ref]: Add missing key/values in the json files.

In api-ref/source/v3/samples, some of JSON file contents does not
match the current v3 input or output, This patch is to update the
Request and Response JSON contents.

Change-Id: Ib6f0fcb9dc476f77b20cd780cfc6e8e1e425f4e1

commit_message:
Bump minimum os-testr version to 1.0.0

This commit bumps the minimum requirement of os-testr to 1.0.0. This new
release changes the test runner used internally to stestr. Since this is
a major internal change it'll be better to switch it early in the cycle
to shake loose any potential bugs.

Change-Id: Iabe4217c6aa52cb4d3a715756e0b8c46a6d553d0

commit_message:
Only do etcd3 config if service is enabled

Devstack is setting etcd3 vars even though the etcd3 service disabled.
This causes devstack on s390x to fail as no etcd3 binary for s390x is
available. The workaround till [1] was to just disable the etcd3 service
in local.conf [2][3]. This patch is enabling this workaround again.

[1] https://github.com/openstack-dev/devstack/commit/87943ab88e760598710952598424e7feded88f5c
[2] https://bugs.launchpad.net/devstack/+bug/1693192
[3] https://docs.openstack.org/devstack/latest/configuration.html#kvm-on-s390x-ibm-z-systems

Change-Id: Ifcbc8b990e853a73462fa36590c24e210967e03a
Partial-Bug: #1693192

commit_message:
Retire Packaging Deb project repos

This commit is part of a series to retire the Packaging Deb
project. Step 2 is to remove all content from the project
repos, replacing it with a README notification where to find
ongoing work, and how to recover the repo if needed at some
future point (as in
https://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/drivers.html#retiring-a-project).

Change-Id: I4de52b8b818225083f85fc144fc2963992bdd5e2

commit_message:
Handle keypair not found from metadata server using cells

Fixes https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1592167 for the
cells case. The fix done in https://bugs.launchpad.net/nova/+bug/1592167
only solves the problem when cells are not used at all

Closes-bug: #1592167

Change-Id: Id663b426261150a1cce310cb4a61d9572f78c016

change assert(Not)Equals to assert(Not)Equal

According to http://docs.python.org/2/library/unittest.html
assert(Not)Equals is a deprecated alias of assert(Not)Equal.

Closes-Bug: #1329757
